  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Fernie</strong></p>
<p>Start on the wide, open nursery slope at the base of the lower mountain and progress to the longer, winding trails from the summit to the base of the lifts.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Fernie</strong></p>
<p>Intermediates will enjoy all areas of the resort and those looking for new challenges should try some glade skiing or powder skiing on the Cedar and Lizard bowls. To practice your carving turns, the well groomed 'Cruiser' run comes highly recommended.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Fernie</strong></p>
<p>Skiers will never tire of gliding through the glades, flying down chutes and tackling the steep terrain on Lizard and Currie bowl. Real powder hounds should try a day of snowcat sking with a guide.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding skiing in Fernie</strong></p>
<p>Riders can test the extensive all-terrain parks and ride the resort's many gullies, tree-runs and off-piste areas.</p>
<p><strong>Related Links:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="/media/13055110/fernie-alpine-resort.pdf" target="_blank" title="Fernie Alpine Resort">Download your Fernie Alpine Resort Resort Map</a></li>
</ul>]]></generalInformation>
